CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1941 reads: "A Beauty in Hills - There's something in the hills and mountains besides gold, and here's proof. Lovely Marie Conners of Pittsburgh found peace and rest in Schenley Heights recently. Only intrusion was the appearance of a Courier photographer. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Marie Conners wearing dark pleated skirt and trumpet shaped brooch, seated on lawn with trees and University of Pittsburgh Cathedral of Learning in background
